Why is Cornishware called Cornishware? It was created using a nifty lathe-turning technique that scraped blue slip away from its beautiful ceramics to reveal white bands of clay beneath. This tree will always be so special to me. Every ornament was made by a  resident at the assisted living community where I work. I’ve loved everything about working there except the schedule. So…I’m going back to being a Nanny starting next month. I plan on visiting the friends I made as much as I can…they have made an indelible impression on my heart. Most won’t remember me…some still don’t know my name…but sharing their lives these last few months has been a blessing. Most are in their 90’s and are in different stages of dementia. The team I work with are incredible and make it very hard to leave. But…I miss the freedom and flexibility I had to visit our home on Cape Cod. So, this new Nanny position will be perfect for that…🤍 So, enjoy this reel filled with sweet ornaments made with love!
